    "Background": {
      "text": "Inflammation of testis - can be infectious (usually) or non-infectious\nInfectious\nViral\n- most common etiology is\nmumps\n(orchitis seen in 20-30% of mumps patients)\n[1]\nEpididymis typically not involved\nBacterial - typically due to hematogenous spread from\nepididymis\n: \"epididymo-orchitis\"\n(bacterial infections rarely involve only the testis)\nbacterial pathogens:\nN. gonorrhea\n,\nC. trachomatis\n,\nE. Coli\n,\nKlebsiella\n,\nP. aeruginosa",
